   <directions>
      <step><![CDATA[Boil cauliflower in salted water on high heat until al dente, 4m, then drain cool in cold water. Cut in small florets.]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Start cooking the pasta, in the same water.]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Fry the onion in olive on medium heat until wilted, 4m]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Add pine nuts, and fry until slightly browned, 2m]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Add the raisings and cauliflower and fry, 30s]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Add saffron and lower heat. Keep on low simmer until pasta ready, adding water from pasta if it gets too dry]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Heat some olive oil, add the anchovies (or blue cheese) and break with a fork]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[Add the bread crumbs, stirring.]]></step>
      <step><![CDATA[When the pasta is ready drain, mix in the sauce, and sprinkle toasted breadcrums on it.]]></step>
   </directions>
